HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1189
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the University of
Tennessee at Chattanooga Police Department
upon its receipt of the Law Enforcement Partner
of the Year Award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, such individuals comprise the officers and staff of the University of
Tennessee at Chattanooga (UTC) Police Department, who were recently honored with the
Chattanooga Police Department (CPD) Law Enforcement Partner of the Year Award, in
recognition of their outstanding collaboration, professionalism, and commitment to public safety;
and
WHEREAS, the UTC Police is a model partner, providing valuable training, resources,
and expertise and supporting the Chattanooga Police Department's long-term sustainability by
facilitating engagement with UTC's Criminal Justice Department and bolstering recruitment; and
WHEREAS, together the UTC Police and the CPD responded seamlessly to a reported,
though false, active shooter incident on campus, demonstrating strong interagency relations and
unified command; and
WHEREAS, beyond emergencies, UTC Police assists Chattanooga's school patrol
officers in maintaining a safe crosswalk and has been invaluable to CPD's Crime Analysis and
Intelligence Unit, enhancing situational awareness through timely information sharing; and
HJR1189
016018
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the UTC Police Department exemplifies collaboration, measurably and
positively impacting Chattanooga's safety and the Chattanooga Police Department; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga
Police Department upon its receipt of the Law Enforcement Partner of the Year Award from the
Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
